<FIRST>d a PM-CornyLogo     03-23 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Corny Logo,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Farming Community Seeks Less Corny Identity</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUBURN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Corn is king in this small town, but
officials have turned a deaf ear on a proposal to feature the
vegetable in a new city logo.
   Officials met Tuesday at a table lined with corn-emblazoned
coffee mugs that city Administrator Phillip H. Belcher said could be
used to help promote Auburn.
   But leaders opted for a contest to create an easier-to-swallow
emblem, Belcher said.
   ``We're trying to get a little more notoriety,'' he said, adding
that many people never heard of the farming community of 1,900
residents.
   Officials in the town 100 miles north of Detroit will work with
schools this fall to come up with a new logo for road signs,
promotions and a city flag, Belcher said.
</TEXT>
