<SECOND>AM-Alexandria Shootout,210</SECOND>
<HEAD>RETRANSMITTING a0836 to correct category code</HEAD>
<HEAD>Two Killed in Shoot-out</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, VA. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A policeman and an unidentified gunman who
had taken five persons hostage were killed Wednesday in a gun battle
that reportedly began with the gunman trying to obtain cocaine.
   A second Alexandria policeman was shot and seriously wounded and
was undergoing surgery in nearby Washington, D.C., police said.
   The incident began when the man entered a home in the city's
north end Wednesday afternoon and held five persons hostage,
according to police spokesman Joseph Hilleary.
   Police did not say what prompted the incident, but WUSA-TV
reported the man entered the home, demanded crack cocaine, and
threatened to kill the people there unless they supplied it. One
neighbor, who declined to be identified, said the address was known
in the neighborhood as a crack house.
   Police began negotiating with the gunman and the hostages were
released one at a time, Hilleary said.
   The gunman eventually emerged from the backdoor, holding a
shotgun to the head of a hostage and demanding that police drop
their weapons. One officer fired at the gunman, who fired back,
shooting two policeman.
   In the ensuing fight, the hostage escaped unharmed and the gunman
was killed, Hilleary said.
