<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     03-23 0409</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0420</SECOND>
<HEAD>Most of Nation Enjoys Fair Weather</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   High pressure systems along the New England coast and the
Southwest brought fair weather to much of the western, central and
northeastern parts of the nation this morning.
   Elsewhere, an area of low pressure moving across the northern
Gulf of Mexico spread rain across much of the eastern Gulf Coast
region, the Tennessee Valley and the southern Alantic Coast states.
   Thunderstorms dumped up to an inch of rain across portions of
northern Florida. One to 2 inches of snow were expected over the
northern mountains of North Carolina.
   The difference in air pressure between the high off the New
England coast and the low over the northern Gulf of Mexico produced
strong northeast winds along the North Carolina coast.
   Snow was widely scattered over the northern Rockies and Upper
Michigan, where an inch fell at Sault Saint Marie.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from
Alabama across to the southern Atlantic Coast and Florida; rain
mixed with snow in western Montana; and light snow in northeast
Minnesota and northwest Wisconsin.
   Highs were predicted to be in the 30s from northern Minnesota to
Upper Michigan and across northern Maine; 40s and 50s from much of
the Atlantic Coast across the Ohio and Tennessee valleys and the
Great Lakes, the middle Mississippi Valley, southern Minnesota, the
northern Plains and northern Rockies to the Pacific Northwest; 80s
in central and southern florida and from southwest Texas to the
Desert Southwest; and 60s to 70s elsewhere.
   Temperatures at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 5 degrees below zero at
Houlton, Maine, to 76 degrees at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 40 rain; Boston 30 fair; Buffalo 20 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 43 foggy; Cincinnati 32 windy; Cleveland 26 fair;
Detroit 27 fair; Miami 72 fair; New York 34 fair; Philadelphia 29
fair; Pittsburgh 28 partly cloudy; Portland, Maine 20 fair;
Washington 34 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 30 fair; Chicago 35 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 42
fair; Denver 40 partly cloudy; Des Moines 37 partly cloudy;
Indianapolis 32 fair; Kansas City 37 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 33
fair; Nashville 40 cloudy; New Orleans 48 cloudy; St. Louis 36 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 46 fair; Anchorage 31 snow; Las Vegas 58
partly cloudy; Los Angeles 54 partly cloudy; Phoenix 66 fair; Salt
Lake City 47 thunderstorms; San Diego 57 cloudy; San Francisco 51
cloudy; Seattle 38 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 16 fair; Toronto 21 fair.
</TEXT>
