<HEAD>Youth Hears Cries of Mother Who Was Slain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A boy who tried to save his mother's life by
offering a robber $4 listened helplessly from his bedroom as the man
stabbed her to death, police said.
   Joanna Woods, 39, was slain in her home Wednesday by a
knife-wielding man who knocked on the door around 4 a.m. and forced
his way in when she answered, investigators said. The man demanded
money and started beating the woman.
   Her 12-year-old son told police he ran into the living room after
hearing his mother scream, then went to his bedroom and got the only
money he had and offered it to the man, police said.
   The boy told police the man threw it on the floor and said, ``I
don't want that. I want some money.''
   After begging for his mother's safety, the boy was ordered to his
room by the intruder. The boy came out one more time and saw his
mother being stabbed, said homicide Sgt. Terry Ross. When the man
left, the boy called police.
   Woods was stabbed in the chest, arms, hands, face, legs and back,
Ross said.
