<HEAD>Dozens Injured When Trams Collide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two trams collided head-on during the afternoon rush
hour Thursday, injuring more than 30 people, according to news
reports.
   The most seriously injured were the two tram conductors, who were
hospitalized, the reports said.
   Twelve people were treated for injuries at San Giovanni Hospital,
said a police spokesman there. About 20 others were taken to the
Policlinico Hospital, according to a nurse who spoke on condition of
anonymity.
   The accident occurred about 1:30 p.m., when many Romans are
returning home for lunch.
   Initial reports indicated the mechanism to switch one of the
trams onto an alternate line did not work, the ANSA news agency said.
