<HEAD>Jury Convicts Wrestling Coach For Biting Off Man's Earlobe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CROWN POINT, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A high school wrestling coach has been
convicted of a misdemeanor battery charge for biting off part of a
man's ear during a fight that began as a traffic dispute.
   Scott Vlink, 33, coach at Crown Point High School, will be
sentenced April 26 by Judge Nicholas Schiralli in Lake Superior
Court.
   He could be sentenced to up to a year in prison and fined $5,000
in connection with the May 19, 1987, incident on the courthouse
square in Crown Point.
   The jury deliberated about an hour Wednesday before returning the
verdict.
   According to testimony, Vlink bit off Donald Dugger's earlobe
during the altercation which began as Dugger, also of Crown Point,
crossed a street.
   Dugger alleged that a car nearly hit him. He said he made a
kicking motion toward the car, and that the driver, whom he
identified as Vlink, got out and started fighting.
