<HEAD>First Soviet Aircraft in Namibia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINDHOEK, Namibia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Soviet aircraft landed in Namibia on
Thursday for the first time, carrying Finnish troops and crates of
equipment for the U.N. peacekeeping force monitoring the territory's
transition to independence.
   A delegation of U.N. officials were at the Windhoek airport for
