   Volume on the Big Board came to 22.42 million shares as of 10
a.m. on Wall Street.
   International Business Machines rose | to 109~ and Digital
Equipment gained } to 97[. Both stocks came under severe selling
pressure in recent sessions as the Street's earnings expectations
for the companies were scaled back.
   An IBM official said investors had overreacted to a company
statement last week that its earnings for the first quarter would
fall short of analysts' estimates.
   He said the company's expectations for demand for all of 1989
haven't changed.
   IBM and Digital are prominent holdings of many investing
institutions. The woes of those stocks in recent days had raised
concerns about the overall outlook for corporate profits.
   So when the stocks steadied today, brokers said, the mood of the
market in general brightened.
