<HEAD>Gannett Sells Sturgis Newspaper To Arkansas Publishers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STURGIS, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gannett Co. Inc. has sold the Sturgis
Journal to Hometown Communications Inc. of Little Rock, Ark., for an
undisclosed price, the newspaper said Thursday.
   The newspaper, founded in 1859 and owned by Gannett since 1980,
has a daily circulation of approximately 8,500.
   Few other details about the sale were released, and a telephone
call to the home of Hometown Communications President Brent Leslie
was unanswered Thursday morning. There was no business telephone
listing in Little Rock for Hometown Communications. Officials at
Gannett didn't immediately return a phone call.
   The newspaper said Leslie expressed Hometown's enthusiasm about
becoming an active member of the Sturgis community.
   Gannett, based in Washington, D.C., publishes 86 daily newspapers.
