<FIRST>r f BC-AutoProdn     03-23 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0152</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
196,569 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
248,022, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago, in
which 237,295 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 127,636 cars this week,
compared with 152,572 a week ago and 149,951 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 68,933,
compared with last week's 95,450 and last year's 87,344.
   Canadian automakers were to build 18,554 cars this week, down
from 20,195 a week ago and from last year's 26,492.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 16,282, compared
with 17,324 a week ago and 20,266 in the same week last year.
